Format
-Full passage readout.Single correct(FPR_1)
  0.6x -> +5xp for each correct ans
  0.8x -> +8xp for each correct ans

-Full passage readout.Multi correct(FPR_2)
  0.6x -> +10xp for each correct ans

-Full passage readout.Write as many as you can(FPR_3)
  0.6x -> +20xp for each correct ans

-Complete line readout ,with blank spaces to be filled.{options provided}(CLR_1) 
  0.6x -> +2xp for each correct ans
  0.8x -> +3xp for each correct ans

-Complete line readout ,with blank spaces to be filled.{user has to type}(CLR_2) 
  0.6x -> +4xp for each correct ans

-Complete sentence formation, sentence spoken in advance and options provided to help complete form the original sentence.(CSF)
  0.6x -> +8xp for each correct ans

formula of xp 
count of particular q type is represented by its abbreveation
(FPR_1*5  +  FPR_2*10  +  FPR_3*20  +  CLR_1*2  +  CLR_2*4  +  CSF*8) + (FPR_1  + FPR_2  + FPR_3  + CLR_1  +  CLR_2  +  CSF)  *  (SPEED - 0.6)  *  (30/2)

wordCount<time<NoOfQ

